SIMPLE: entertainment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entertainment
<hw>En`ter*tain"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>entretenement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of receiving
as host, or of amusing, admitting, or cherishing; hospitable reception;
also, reception or treatment, in general.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>entertainment</qex> of Christ by faith.</q>
<rj><qau>Baxter.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sincere <qex>entertainment</qex> and practice of the precepts
of the gospel.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Sprat.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which entertains, or with which one is
entertained;</def> <specif>as:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Hospitality;
hospitable provision for the wants of a guest; especially, provision for
the table; a hospitable repast; a feast; a formal or elegant meal.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>That which engages the attention agreeably, amuses or
diverts, whether in private, as by conversation, etc., or in public, by
performances of some kind; amusement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Theatrical <qex>entertainments</qex> conducted with greater
elegance and refinement.</q> <rj><qau>Prescott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Admission into service; service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some band of strangers in the adversary's
<qex>entertainment</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Payment of soldiers or servants; wages.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>entertainment</qex> of the general upon his first arrival
was but six shillings and eight pence.</q> <rj><qau>Sir J.
Davies.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Amusement; diversion; recreation; pastime; sport;
feast; banquet; repast; carousal.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entertake</ent>⟦br⟧
